and i did our first  livestream EVER on thursday and it was so awesome!!

huge shoutout to , , , , Andrea,  and everyone else who i can't find on farcaster 

will put some thoughts & highlights in this thread ‚¨áÔ∏è

1/ we had a really wide range of perspectives on wallets, from designers/pms/growth people working full time in crypto to people with no experience with wallets at all

we talk about ux a lot in crypto but it was interesting to me what power users noticed versus new users

2/ this üî• insight from  - the current wallet experience is like requiring someone to spin up a bank account before entering a museum (to mint nfts, invest, etc)

when wallets exist entirely separately from where people can do things in crypto it introduces more friction!

3/ which leads to this comment from  - wallets just become the browser!

it's super annoying to have to connect a wallet and go back and forth between a browser and wallet app on mobile, and the wallet browser is huge for this - i use the  browser all the time to avoid this back and forth!

4/ one other great insight that  had was about the visual hierarchy of onboarding flows - we looked at examples of wallets with longer vs shorter flows, overlays, and other details but not overwhelming the user is key to helping them set up their wallet successfully

5/ finally, a huge shoutout to my partners in crime  and  for cohosting with me. maria did an amazing job leading the session!
